name: Creative Ink Painting
description: Participants will use natural elements as inspiration for their Creative Ink Painting - branches, leaves, flowers, seashells, seed pods & grasses.All materials are provided for the class, including ink, paper, brushes; and a collection of natural items to choose from as the subject matter for your artwork. Workshop is open to participants aged 16 years old and above. Children are welcome, though will need to be accompanied by a parent/guardian. Please register each person who will attend the workshop

name: Wyndham Business Network - A New Way To Network
description: Wyndham Business Network is a not for profit networking group in Melbourne's West connecting local businesses and creating referable relationships.Our meetings have returned to an in person meeting format commencing at 7:15am. If you would like to visit the group please register for your free ticket and we will email you with further meeting information. The team meet fortnightly Wednesday morning from 7.15am to 8:45am at Level 1, 5 Wedge Street, Werribee.

name: Paradigm Festival 2021
description: We are very proud of what we have able to achieve considering all the challenges of a global pandemic All our artists will be quarantining upon entering Australia and are beyond excited to perform for you! Due to people consistently selling fake tickets and tickets at inflated prices, we have partnered up with Tixel to secure all ticket resells and swaps. The name on your ticket must match your ID upon entry and Tixel is the only place to ensure this takes place

name: Riva Night Party - Rebūke
description: A soundclash of house, techno and rave records from the early 90s melded together, Rebūke is an international artist building a distinct sound of his own. Supporting this elusive heavy-hitter is Boogs, Black Tiger, Carina Lawrence and Tiff Cornish. This event will take place in a heated marquee at Riva St Kilda - a premier bayside destination with panoramic views located under sweeping palms.
